# Help: Advanced NFS server features (NFSv4, pNFS)
#
# Self-contained: inlines fs/nfs.config's NFSD so it composes on the
# base alone. Adds NFSv4 server support
# (NFSD_V4), the NFSv3 ACL protocol extension, NFSv4.2
# inter-server-to-server copy (NFSD_V4_2_INTER_SSC), and the
# three pNFS layout types (block, SCSI, flex-file) used by
# pynfs and pNFS testing workflows.
#
# NFSD_V4_SECURITY_LABEL requires CONFIG_SECURITY=y; SECURITY is
# inlined here so the fragment composes standalone. When
# security/security.config is also layered, the value matches and
# there is no conflict.
# NFSD_PNFS is an internal bool without a user prompt; it is
# auto-selected by any NFSD_*LAYOUT symbol.
#
# All symbols are bool and parent on tristate NFSD, which
# Kconfig permits with NFSD=m. No builtin/ counterpart is
# needed.
# See: fs/nfsd/Kconfig
# See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/filesystems/nfs/index.html
# See: https://github.com/kolyshkin/pynfs

#
# Inlined prerequisites (fs/nfs.config NFSD; SECURITY for the
# NFSD_V4_SECURITY_LABEL bool below)
#
CONFIG_NFSD=m
CONFIG_SECURITY=y

CONFIG_NFSD_V3_ACL=y
CONFIG_NFSD_V4=y
CONFIG_NFSD_V4_2_INTER_SSC=y
CONFIG_NFSD_V4_SECURITY_LABEL=y
CONFIG_NFSD_BLOCKLAYOUT=y
CONFIG_NFSD_SCSILAYOUT=y
CONFIG_NFSD_FLEXFILELAYOUT=y
